Hey <@UGMGP7A72> sure thing.

so for example, here is how I have it set up in the HTML to search one specific blog

```{# Need help setting up site search?
   Start here: <https://knowledge.HubSpot.com/articles/kcs_article/cos-general/how-do-i-set-up-a-results-page-for-my-search-field-in-HubSpot> #}
&lt;section class="searchResults"&gt;
  &lt;div class="container"&gt;
    &lt;div class="hs-search-field"&gt; 
        &lt;div class="hs-search-field__bar"&gt; 
          &lt;form action="<http://www-visioncritical-com.sandbox.hs-sites.com/blog-search-results-alida>"&gt;
            {% if module.field_label %}
              &lt;label for="term"&gt;{{ module.field_label }}&lt;/label&gt;
            {% endif %}
            &lt;input type="text" class="hs-search-field__input" name="term" autocomplete="off" aria-label="{{ module.field_label || "Search" }}" placeholder="Search the blog"&gt;
            &lt;input type="hidden" name="groupID" value="34129208273"&gt; 
            {% if module.include_search_button %}
              &lt;button aria-label="Search"&gt;{% icon name="search" style="solid" %}&lt;/button&gt;
            {% endif %}
          &lt;/form&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;ul class="hs-search-field__suggestions"&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;```
